content.detailedDescription:
As we my wife and i walked down the beach today i looked up in the sky. because of my interest in the sky i have often witnessed all kinds of planes, satellites, comets and chinese lanterns etc. 

i have been tested several times for my vision which always results in a 100%. i got tested last time in 2005 before i immigrated to the state and i'm certain that it's just as good now as it was back then. 

what i saw today was something new to me. the object appeared to be sphere like and seamed to be randomly wobbling. much like in this footage [link moved to field investgator section/cms/tg] but, it was too far away for me to be sure that it was more than one object.

when i first noticed it, i thought at first it was just another plane because there where already several other airplanes in the air. so the chances of a pilot having noticed it as well are good. after a few seconds i realized it wasn't moving.

after a few seconds of observation i noticed that it was moving but very slowly. it moved south slower than a satellite, in fact it moved so slow that it was hard to observe that it was moving at all. than after a while when it was right above the beach it turned west. 

since it was so slow it wasn't an abrupt 90 degree turn, but it seam very determined in its direction before and after the turn. further more it seamed to be changing its altitude because it became smaller in size.

the fog came in from the see side and it was hard to see it at all thereafter. i also had to leave at that point and unfortunately stopped observing it.

the whole time i was wishing for someone with a camera to walk by because i haven't had mine with me and a zoom would have come very handy. unfortunately i couldn't spot one. 

still i have no idea what it was that i saw and i tried to see if maybe somebody had uploaded footage at youtube but found non so far.
content.summary: Strange white object above santa cruz (ca) harbor

content.detailedDescription:
Our ship, the carnival glory had left halifax, nova scotia, canada and was on its way back to new york, city. we had just finished dinner and went to our cabin which had a balcony on the starboard side of the ship on deck 9. 

i went out onto the balcony to have a smoke and it was pretty stormy. couldn't see any other objects except the sea and the misty dark sky. all of a sudden a well defined pill shaped object with a dull glow went in a perfectly straight line from the front of the ship to the back. when it reached the back it took a sudden turn downward and i thought it was going to go into the sea but instead it curved around the back of the ship. this only took about 10 seconds from start to finish. i couldn't believe what i saw and debated whether or not i should report it. 

i stayed out on the balcony for about twenty more minutes hoping it would return but it never did. i told my wife but did not report it to the ships crew because i thought they would think i was some kind of a nut. i currently live in las vegas just 90 miles from area 51 and i have never seen anything like this before. i want to be clear that it didn't look metallic. it was closer to being some kind of dull light or energy but shaped like a pill with crisp edges. i am a web designer and self trained graphic artist and have done my best to recreate what i saw. i just wish someone else would have filed a report and i could have backed up their report.
content.summary: Pill shaped dull glowing object at sea

content.detailedDescription: Silent, bright white light travelling all the way from the ssw (saw it at around 30 degrees above the horizon) to the een direction (disappeared around 15 degrees above the horizon behind the mountain/tree line). straight line trajectory. about the size of an asprin held at arms length. witnessed by myself, youngest son (20 - chemist major) and daughter (17 - senior in high school and college student). tried to video tape it with my kodak easyshare c433 camera in video mode, but the quality is very bad. this was not a sun reflection off of an airplane as there were several flying in the air as well from a ene to a wsw direction along the normal flight path and all you see from them were there normal lights flashing. their sounds could be heard as well. sighting last approx. 10 minutes from start to finish. did not notice that the other aircraft acknowledge this light as none of them altered their courses. i'm ex-usaf (341st wing headquarters, malmstrom afb, great falls, mt), educated (b.Sc.) and have been in r & d for over 20 years - i'm used to looking up at the sky. ps: keep in mind that the video quality is very bad due to the type of camera used. the lights at the bottom left (2 - 3 of them at times) are not the object. i tried to keep in somewhere near the center of the video. you'll see it near the middle the first minute or two in the center. this was shot after the ufo had attained a 90 degree view from me, so already partially into the sighting. you will hear myself and children talking near the end as well.
content.summary: Bright light, asprin size, 10 minutes from horizon to horizon, 7:10 pm

content.detailedDescription:
i got a text from a friend in villa park il who said he was watching a star like object hover in his neighborhood. villa park is 11 miles west of where i am so i decided to go outside to my backyard and sky watch. it was a clear night not much going on at first. then out of the northern sky i noticed a small dim orange orb ufo flying south at 715pm and began recording it until it was out of view. i looked down and sent a text to my friend that i had just caught a fireball orb flying over me when i looked back up there was the biggest brightest orb ufo i have seen yet. i have seen different types of ufos flying by day and night for over 2 years but this one was one of the closest and brightest i have ever encountered. it made no noise and was amazingly big bright white light. it was in the shape of a large ball hovering over the tree top. i immediately put my camera on it and starting recording. this was at 717pm. it started to move east toward the city. i got my butt of my zero gravity lawn chair and ran to my right to keep recording it. it kept moving behind a tree so i ran back to the left to see if i could keep recording it but it had disappeared. 

  i sat back down and sent my friend another text saying i just saw a big bright white orb hovering and waited to see if more would show. about 13 minutes went by and i saw another high quick moving dim orange star like ufo this time flying south to north. i recorded the best i could as i am still a novice trying to film these things. 3 minutes later a second star-like ball of light flew in the same south to north path over the sky at probably the same height speed and distance. 

  i have no idea what they are if they are man made, natural to this world, or et. my guess is et. but as i mentioned that have been coming out more often and frequently day and night by where i live. to view my video search multiple star-like ufos chicago 16 october 2011 on youtube. i attached a few pics below of the big bright one. 

  i use the youtube channel name guttergawker if you want to look at the other uploads of ufos i have caught. on oct 9th i caught a few day time green diamond shaped ufos flying over and have good close up video of those craft. sorry about the name guttergawker, i signed up for youtube long before i began to see ufos and would just watch crap on youtube hence the name. and sorry about all the shake in the video i try and stabilize what i catch as much as possible but it never comes out to smooth. i tried using a tripod but its ever harder to record these things flying across the sky with one. and i never know from which direction or what time they will show up so when i do see them i do my best keeping the camera on them but it moves around alot when i have the focus set on infinity and zoom 300xs. 

  anyways thanks for reading, if you live in chicago watch the skies on clear starry nights after 7pm and i am sure you'll see what i am seeing.
content.summary: Multiple star-like ufos over chicago from 715 to 745pm hd video

content.detailedDescription: I'm a 30 year old, married man. i was alone with my dog outside in olathe, ks around 6:45am on the morning of monday, october 17, 2011. i walked around my apartment building to the north and turned the corner into a small, open field. that is when i saw a stationary, flashing light hovering above the distant horizon to the northeast. it pulsated -- changing from a small pin-point of light to a bright light and back again within about a 2 second time-frame. it did this on a regular interval the entire time i was out there. it did not look like a helicopter or airplane, as there were no other flashing lights that you might find on most man-made aircraft. and it appeared to be completely still and stationary. i've also never seen a helicopter or airplane pulsate with light in such a way. after about 10 seconds of watching this light, i ran back inside and grabbed my camera. i came back out and began video-taping the light. from my perspective, and my familiarity with the surrounding kansas city area, i would guess that the light was somewhere above the overland park, ks area, north of i-435. i live just to the southeast of the i-35 & i-435 interchange. the light could have been as close as a mile or two away from me, or as far as several miles. it was difficult to estimate how far it was, as i didn't see a solid object associated with the flashing light. it was so still that it looked like a flashing light mounted atop a tall radio tower, but there is no such tower in that spot. after video-taping the light for a little over a minute, i turned the camera off and went back inside. i didn't feel like there was much point in sticking around, as the light's behavior never changed. i went inside for about 5-10 minutes. when i came back outside to see if the light was still there, it was gone.
content.summary: Stationary, flashing light hovering above the distant horizon to the northeast of where i stood.

content.detailedDescription: I was outside smoking a cigarette in front of my dorm.  i was looking at the sky because there were 4 spotlights making figure 8 patterns from the roof some night club or something to the east.  that's when i noticed what looked like a star moving.  it was mostly white but it had different green and blue colors kind of flashing but maintaining a constant luminosity.  i thought it was a satellite.  then i saw 2 more of the same making a large triangle and they were all moving with uniform speed and and keeping the same relative distance to one another.  i thought it was some sort of plane formation because i'm right near an airport.  then i saw two more to make it an even bigger triangle.  still moving with uniform speed and same distance from one another. the speed and distance were too uniform and the too far apart for them not to be somehow connected i thought.  but the space between them just looked like dark starless sky.  i thought maybe it was some kind of stealth bomber type of craft but it would have to be giant.  then it stopped for about 5 min.  then i thought i was just seeing things so i waved to it and laughed to myself. but, a couple minutes later, it started moved in a slightly different direction and i stopped doubting myself.  it seemed to move relatively slow but much faster than any of the stars.  a plane did fly by under it on the way to the airport and that seemed to be much faster but it was also much much closer.  the original direction was from east to west directly over my head but after it stopped it took a more northwest direction.  i went inside to grab a camera with a video option because my crappy phone doesn't take video and a still picture would have just looked like stars (if it took a visible picture at all) but when i returned it was gone.  i went back out every hour or so after that with my camera until about 1 in the morning but didnt't see anything else.

content.detailedDescription:
At 7:40pm, i was heading home on i-235 near the 14th street exit, when i saw something that resembled an object on fire. it was a reddish-orange light, about the exact color of fire, and was traveling in a northerly direction. i stopped the car on the off ramp and got out for a better look.
 
there was a nearly full moon behind me as i watched the light move across the sky. i hold a private pilot's license, and although at this time i am not "current", i've been around aircraft all my life, and i've never seen anything like this. there was a thin/broken layer of clouds i estimated to be about 4,000 to 5,000 feet above ground level. the light was below the clouds.
 
i applied 'critical thinking' in my attempt to identify the light. i asked myself "why couldn't this be _____?"
 
no aircraft i know of produces a reddish-orange light. plus there were no position, navigation, or anti-collision lights visible. also, this was not a landing light, as it was omni-directional, not shining ahead as a landing light would.
 
then i considered it may have been the rosat satellite, which is due to re-enter the atmosphere and burn up. the light had no firey trail in it's wake, and it appeared to be traveling in straight and level flight.
 
also the light appeared to be moving fast, so this was no "oriental lantern". i would guess the light was about 3,000 feet, and traveled from horizon to horizon in less than 90 seconds.
content.summary: A small glowing reddish-orange sphere

content.detailedDescription: I was at a friends house for a bonfire on a saturday night. while sitting with my girlfriend and chatting with friends i noticed 4 lights (satelite sized) that made a triangle flying in a straight path over the property we were on. i noticed it at first because i always enjoy watching the sky and thought it was a satelite but never seen them so close together so i knew it was something other-worldly.  i had a feeling it was a ufo but you just never really expect to get such proof. all 4 lights stayed uniform as it flew south to north overhead of myself as well as several other witnesses. i yelled "look! what's that?" astonished. as everyone just watched for maybe 15 seconds as it kept going out of sight. about a minute later, in the same flight path and direction, a swarm of at least 30 single lights all bunched together came overhead. all i could do was watch in awe as this swarm of starlike lights buzzed silently flying south to north. i distinctively remember keeping my eye on two lights that were on the outer rim of the swarm, i watched one bounce over blocking my view of the other and then back again in less then a second. all the lights just kept going at a steady speed (about that of a satelite) and disappeared out of view. i felt like i had just seen something that i will probably never get to see again. i was upset that no one had any video proof, but was super estatic to have my own proof after observing the night sky and wondering what if for so long.
content.summary: Huge swarm of 30+ starlike lights flying south to north

content.detailedDescription:
I took my dogs out before going to bed. i looked up and noticed what i thought was a bright star. as i was standing there it appeared to come closer to me and became much larger. i could not see an outline with the naked eye it was very bright. i took pictures with my cell phone and upon reviewing the picture it appeared to have a rectangle shape.

i became overwhelmed with anxiety. because of this i left my home to spend the night with my daughter, and as i was leaving it retreated to a higher location. as i was going to my vehicle my dog started barking at something in the shadows. 

the object/light was visible for a six hours, changing position twice. it was obvious because my reference was the moon. 

the object was positioned in the east near the moon, and repositioned itself twice moving south then west further from the moon.

i felt like something was outside for most of the night and could not go to sleep. at 5:00am, it was still dark, the anxiety just lifted.

i continued to check for the object hourly. at 5:30am when i looked for it, it was gone. though the moon was still visible.

the object is small, and is situated in the center of the photo.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving from store then i was comeing to a stop sign looked left and then right when i look right before i got to stop sign i noticed a bright light in sky like a search light but bigger and brighter just hovering in sky i keep watching and it was like it noticed me looking and just went in a straight line no noise so fast it was amazing i was stunned i tried to follow it instantly going as fast as i could if it was a plane i would have saw it i was born and raised in pittsfield mass no were the airport is etc clear sky very clear and i was takeing streets to give me access to it and at no time after it took off did i see again just dissappeared awesome no noise i was so close i told a few people and my wife got up this morning and check local newspaper then went to google and googled pittsfield mass ufo sightings and to my surprise there have been several that i did not no about over the last few month's. there has to be many people who saw this right over residential neighborhood impossible for people not to see this.
content.summary: I was driving comeing to stop sign look left right and saw a bright light in sky stopped  and watched light was so bright it was just hovering and then it was like it noticed me looking and took off in a straight line so fast it was amazing tired to chase

content.detailedDescription: These clouds were in front of me as i drove west towards fresno, cal. pictures were taken by my passenger at my request...Reviewing the pictures later i noticed things i had not seen or realised at first. not only does the large cloud have what appears to be a swirling extension vapor trail like swirl benieth it...But the other two clouds have circular swirls in thier center and...In upper right of large cloud in one of the photos there is a shiny translucent disc shaped object that is at an angle tipping into the cloud. wanted your opinions. i have a few more pictures of the same...Some through the windshield and some from out the window
content.summary: Saw these clouds as i was driving towards fresno and had my passenger take the pictures
